  m_text: A harsh, mechanical wail echoes through cold metal walls, pulsing in time
    with a dull ache in your head. The air smells stale, like dust and something
    faintly metallic. You push yourself upright from the floor, your vision swimming.
    For a moment, there is nothing. No name. No past. Just the noise.
